Class PairwiseSummaryTableModel

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, TableModel
public class PairwiseSummaryTableModel
extends SummaryTableModel

PairwiseSummaryTableModel is the subclass of SummaryTableModel used for tables derived from pairwise IDEA analyses (those for which all datasets have exactly two sequences). These analyses differ from non-pairwise analyses in that multiple models for site-class evolution are not used. Therefore, there is only one set of results for each dataset. For simplicity, the same data structure is used for all summary table models; for pairwise models, each vector of vectors of objects representing a dataset contains only one vector of objects. Pairwise data tables contain two extra columns (dN and dS, the rates of nonsynonymous and synonymous substitutions, respectively). PairwiseSummaryTableModel provides a constructor that loads data from a file in PAML's unique pairwise output format.

PairwiseSummaryTableModel

public PairwiseSummaryTableModel(String dirName,
                                 File[] mlcFiles,
                                 edu.umaryland.igs.aegan.utils.SwingThreadSafeComponent<JProgressBar> progress)
                          throws IOException
This creates a PairwiseSummaryTableModel from data in files in the specified directory. It is called by the load method in SummaryTableModel when pairwise data is detected.

Parameters:
dirName - the directory containing the .mlc files to use
mlcFiles - the pre-sorted list of .mlc files in the directory
progress - a progress bar to update as loading progesses; may be null
Throws:
IOException - if an output file is deleted while data is being loaded or an I/O error occurs

leftmostColumnToDisplayAsSelected

public int leftmostColumnToDisplayAsSelected()
Row selection is indicated on the table by displaying an outline around all or some of the row's cells. The leftMostColumnToDisplayAsSelected method returns the index of the leftmost column to be included in the outlined area when a row is selected. PairwiseSummaryTableModel's implementation returns 0 because in pairwise tables, no columns contain values that span multiple rows.

Specified by:
leftmostColumnToDisplayAsSelected in class SummaryTableModel
Returns:
the index of the Model column
